Package lavaplayer

Class TrackScheduler

  • java.lang.Object
    • lavaplayer.TrackScheduler
  • public class TrackScheduler
extends java.lang.Object
    This class schedules tracks for the audio player. It contains the queue of tracks.

      • getQueue

        public java.util.List<Track> getQueue()
        Returns the queue for this scheduler. Adding to the head of the queue (index 0) does not automatically cause it to start playing immediately. The returned collection is thread-safe and can be modified. To iterate over this queue, use a synchronized block. For example: synchronize (getQueue()) { // iteration code }
        Returns:
        The queue.
